Date:  0/0/1930
Source:  Early Canterbury Runs
Author:  ACLAND
Vol / Page:
Edition:
Quote:  Originally only applied to sheep by a longwool ram from a merino ewe, but now loosely applied

to the type. Corriedale sheep were originally called  in-bred half-breds. Now in-bred halfbred flocks are those which reintroduce merino or longwool blood, while the Corriedale flocks can only introduce Corriedale blood.
Notes:  (1890-1910)

